=== 5.5 The Code: Positional Encoding in Python

The matrix data abstraction from Chapter 2 carries over unchanged.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=matrix]
----

The frequency stem:[\omega_k = 1/10000^{2k/d}] controls how fast dimension-pair stem:[k] oscillates with position.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=positional_encoding]
----

`pe-value` is the atomic formula: one number at position stem:[t], dimension stem:[i], in a stem:[d]-dimensional encoding.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=positional_encoding]
----

A full positional encoding vector for position stem:[t] is stem:[d] calls to `pe-value`, one per dimension.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=positional_encoding]
----

The full PE matrix applies `positional-encoding-row` to each of the stem:[T] positions.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=positional_encoding]
----

Adding PE to the token embedding matrix stem:[X] gives stem:[\tilde{X} = X + PE], element-wise.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/chapter_demos.py[tag=chapter_05]
----

Run with `python3 src/python/chapter_demos.py`.

Figure <<fig-ch05-code-pe-matrix>> shows the positional encoding matrix whose rows are added to token embeddings.
[[fig-ch05-code-pe-matrix]]
.Positional encoding matrix
image::images/ch03_pe_matrix.png[Positional encoding matrix — each row is added to the corresponding token embedding.]

Figure <<fig-ch05-code-sin-waves>> shows how sinusoidal waves at different frequencies encode positions across dimensions.
[[fig-ch05-code-sin-waves]]
.Sinusoidal positional frequencies
image::images/ch03_sin_waves.png[Sinusoidal waves at different frequencies encode position uniquely across dimensions.]
